  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Post-operative tissue oedema is one of the main causes of failure of hypospadias repair.
      Severe oedema may disrupt the suture line, invite infection and result in repair failure.
      Thus, we suggested that local injection of corticosteroids in just below coronal sulcus into
      dartos and buck's fascia may limit this oedema thus improving the outcome of hypospadias
      repair.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective comparative trial : comparing the use of local steroids injection to
      reduce tissue edema after hypospadias and to preserve the final cosmesis after tissue repair.

      The patients will be divided into 2 groups(each group 20 patients): one group will be
      injected steroids just after hypospadias surgery while the other will not.

      The short and long term outcomes between both groups will be compared.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
